    "creation_date" : 1606741871,
    "answer_id" : 65074249,
    "question_id" : 2369967,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>if you are trying to check that in spring framework then <code>isEmpty(Object[])</code> method in <code>ObjectUtils</code> class helps,</p>\n<pre><code>public static boolean isEmpty(@Nullable Object[] array) {\n        return (array == null || array.length == 0);\n    }\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4310986,
      "reputation" : 94,
      "user_id" : 3522040,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLe2VNwK8D3JHRrtx5coTpIbBXbyNGAgYzfkUUPocrCGZY=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Yunus",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3522040/yunus"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1705818703,
    "last_edit_date" : 1705818703,
    "creation_date" : 1705817986,
    "answer_id" : 77853783,
    "question_id" : 2369967,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>By 'empty array' most probably you meant length is 0.</p>\n<pre><code>if( array.length == 0 ) {\n    // do something ...\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>But it's also worth to check first if the array ref is <code>null</code> or not before accessing it's property (e.g. <code>length</code>).</p>\n<pre><code>if( array != null ) {\n   if( array.length == 0 ) {\n      // do something ...\n   }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>And this become necessary if the array is a parameter to a method.</p>\n<pre><code>public boolean isEmpty( Object[] array ) throws Exception {\n    if( array != null ) {\n        if( array.length == 0 )\n            return true;\n    } else {\n        throw new Exception(&quot;isEmpty(): Array ref is null&quot;);\n    }\n    return false;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>The checking should be done in cascading way (not using <code>&amp;&amp;</code> i.e. <code>array != null &amp;&amp; array.length == 0</code>) since the order of evaluation of the conditions depends on implementation of the compiler. If it is evaluating the <code>array.length == 0</code> condition first, it will ends with runtime error if <code>array</code> is null.</p>\n"
